I am back from a wonderfully family filled rejuvenating vacation! Spending time with my nieces and nephew, my sister, and my own teens, swimming, hiking, creating treasure hunts, games, and exploring in the woods, dog races,  egg runs, biking, and way too much good food was just what I needed! I am ready to jump back in back to capturing interiors and spaces! I dug into the archives for this one which seems a perfect transition. I photographed this in the home of the Canadian novelist, Erika de Vasconcelos a few years ago. I love how she mirrors the wallpaper with the view out the window! How is your summer going!  #interiorphotography #architecturalphotography #interiordesign

Sometimes you sort through your work, and decide a piece deserves another look. Slide to second shot_(as I originally shot it)This space, shot with @sachanizamidesign a few years ago is one that hit home for me because of its eclectic and authentic feel. There was minimal styling done. We just moved a few items around and placed them to work with the composition. What you see is how @medora2014 lived in the space. The design pieces are the stunning mantel and mirror, which integrate so well with its surroundings. So, I came across this as scrolling through work, and thought a more intimate crop would do more justice, or at least add to its voice. What do you think? Which version works for you? Sometimes, like a painting, a photographed moment can still be in progress.  #interior #exlecticinteriors #mantel #marble #interiordesign #interiorphotography #interiorstyle #vintage #artistic #rose #fireplace #interiorliving #verandastyle #verandamag #ilovemyjob #architecture
